  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (configuration gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The CFD solver employs three tunable configuration parameters: base mesh edge length (h_base), hemolysis scalar transport relaxation factor (alpha_HT), and the power-law exponent threshold for red-blood-cell damage accumulation (tau_thresh). Validation studies were executed at the settings chosen by the analyst at the time of the validation campaign; those results are reported in the validation records. However, no configuration-binding node is linked to this package, and the Context of Use does not constrain which parameter values must be used at deployment. A downstream integrator selecting a coarser mesh, a different relaxation factor, or an alternate damage threshold would obtain a device that has not been validated at those settings, yet the credibility package would still report 'Accepted'.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-worst-case-hemolysis",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-centrifugal-bp-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-cpb-geometry-v2",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/cpb-bench-hemolysis-measurements-2023",
