      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Scalar transport relaxation factor sensitivity — hemolysis scalar convergence",
      "description": "Iterative convergence of the hemolysis scalar transport equation was confirmed with relaxation factor alpha_HT = 0.7 at the chosen settings. Residuals dropped below 1e-6 within 800 iterations across all five operating points. The relaxation factor is documented only in the analyst's run log; it is not linked as a pinned configuration parameter in this credibility package.",
      "quantityOfInterest": "Hemolysis scalar residual norm",
      "passFail": "Pass"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/cpb-vr-03-damage-threshold",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Power-law damage accumulation threshold validation against bench data",
      "description": "The power-law exponent threshold tau_thresh governing onset of red-blood-cell damage accumulation was set to 1.8 Pa during the validation campaign. Predicted RH values at all five flow-speed conditions agreed with bench-measured plasma free haemoglobin to within 12% (acceptance criterion: 15%). Results are reported at the chosen settings. The value of tau_thresh is mentioned in the validation narrative but is not bound to any configuration node in this package; a deployer may select a different value without triggering a re-assessment flag.",
      "quantityOfInterest": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) vs. bench pFHb",
